.NET Core 1.0.name: DiscordGuildChannel
.NET Core 1.0.summary: Guild channels represent an isolated set of users and messages within a DiscordGuild.

constructors.name: DiscordGuildChannel(IDiscordClient client, DiscordGuild guild)
constructors.syntax: public void DiscordGuildChannel(IDiscordClient client, DiscordGuild guild)

methods.name: ConnectToVoice()
methods.summary: Attempts to connect to this voice channel. This is a non-blocking call.

exceptions.value: Thrown if this channel is not a voice channel.

methods.name: Modify(DiscordGuildChannelModifyParams modifyParams)

exceptions.value: Thrown if the params are for a different type of guild channel.

methods.name: ToString()
methods.summary: Gets a string representation of this channel.
methods.returns: Returns the string representation of this channel.

methods.name: Update(DiscordApiData data)

params.value: The data to update this channel with.

properties.name: Bitrate
properties.summary: Gets the bitrate of this channel (if a voice channel).

properties.name: Guild
properties.summary: Gets the guild this channel is in.

properties.name: GuildChannelType
properties.summary: Gets the type of this guild channel.

properties.name: IsPrivate
properties.summary: Gets whether or not this channel is private.

properties.name: LastMessageId
properties.summary: Gets the id of the last message sent in this channel (if a text channel).

properties.name: MemberPermissionOverwrites
properties.summary: All DiscordOverwrites for the DiscordGuildMembers in this channel's guild.
properties.syntax: public Dictionary<DiscordOverwrite, string> MemberPermissionOverwrites { get; set; }

properties.name: Position
properties.summary: Gets the ordering position of this channel.

properties.name: RolePermissionOverwrites
properties.syntax: public Dictionary<DiscordOverwrite, string> RolePermissionOverwrites { get; set; }

properties.name: UserLimit
properties.summary: Gets the user limit of this channel (if a voice channel).
